NEIGHBORHOOD EATERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By APRIL JACKSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Salerno, 220 Beach St., Laguna Beach. Open 11:30 a.m. to 10 p.m. Wednesday 
through Monday. (714) 497-2600. Owner Tony Manzi's accent is nearly as thick as 
his meat sauce, and his menu is just as hearty. 
</P>
<P>
Try the gnocchi, baked mostaccoli with Italian sausage or, if you happen to be 
dining with understanding friends, the fettuccine with garlic and oil. 
</P>
<P>
Las Barcas Mexican Restaurant, 21032 Beach Blvd., Huntington Beach. Open daily, 
11 a.m. to 9 p.m. (714) 536-2616. Oversize portions, the hodgepodge decor and a 
colorful variety of local folk make this tiny eatery a beachside winner. The 
food is good and cheap, featuring ranchero sauce-covered burritos, fresh 
snapper tacos and homemade tortilla chips. Be prepared to take out, though, as 
there's always a crowd. 
</P>
<P>
Sonic Drive-In, 15640 Brookhurst St., Westminster, and 1632 N. Lemon St., 
Anaheim. Both open Sunday through Thursday, 10 a.m. to midnight; Friday and 
Saturday till 1 a.m. (714) 531-8000. Nearly every aspect of this drive-in is 
perfect. From the Texas-size drinks (even the straws are big) to the 
bodaciously hot-to-handle onion rings and juicy hickory burgers. Pull in 
underneath the turquoise-and-white canopy, park next to a squawk box and order 
up. APRIL JACKSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
