</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM WASHBURN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Henry N' Harry's Goat Hill Tavern, 1830 Newport Blvd., Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Open daily from 11 a.m. to 2 a.m. (714) 548-8428. This place serves no fewer 
than 96 brands of tap beer; the keg room looks like Jerry Lee Lewis' idea of a 
well-stocked bomb shelter. The tavern proper consists of several rooms, packed 
with games and decorated with everything from buffalo heads to Elvis dolls. 
Best of all, there are, to quote a regular, "people from all over the world 
here, all kinds, slobs and business people, and they let it all down." JIM 
WASHBURN 
</P>
</TEXT>
