<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE CORNER BAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK MOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
That Other Place, 1615 E. 17th St., Santa Ana. Open 11 a.m. to midnight Monday 
through Thursday, Friday till 2 a.m., and Saturday 5 p.m. to 2 a.m. Closed 
Sunday. (714) 547-9511. 
</P>
<P>
Cocktail lounges are made for tete-a-tetes with your sweetie, or for solo 
imbibing when you want to be serene and contemplative. They should have low 
lights, a low ceiling, intimate seating and lots of stuff to absorb sound and 
keep hushed conversations hushed. This one may be the coziest of the cozy. 
</P>
<P>
Joe Jost's, 2803 E. Anaheim St., Long Beach. Open Monday through Saturday 10 
a.m. to 11 p.m., Sunday 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. (213) 439-5446. In the early 1920s it 
was a barbershop, serving root beer and sandwiches to waiting customers. When 
Prohibition ended, the health department said either serve food and beer or cut 
hair. The beer still comes in frosted 20-ounce schooners, the eggs are pickled 
on the premises, there's pool and snooker in the back room, and freshly roasted 
peanuts and cigars are sold behind the bar. PATRICK MOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
