<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEACHERS DON'T HAVE SAME BENEFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have 20 years of experience, I hold one degree and three credentials, and 
have averaged teaching 200 students each day at Newbury Park High School. 
</P>
<P>
Our district administrators interact with an average of 15 people a day and 
they have a secretary. They receive more money plus, when they retire, they 
receive full medical coverage, yet teachers do not. 
</P>
<P>
The Conejo Valley Unified School District has asked, and expects, its employees 
to work under a contract that allows the district to void key sections of the 
agreement. 
</P>
<P>
Cost-of-living raises average 7%, while we are being asked by the CVUSD to 
accept 4%. 
</P>
<P>
JOAN CHASE 
</P>
<P>
Camarillo 
</P>
</TEXT>
