<P>
New Offer Made for Hotel Investors: A group led by New York investor Leonard M. 
Ross, who has stalked Hotel Investors Trust for the past year, has made an 
offer to acquire the Los Angeles-based hotel owner and operator. The proposal 
by Ross, who owns 9.8% of the paired stock of Hotel Investors Trust and Hotels 
Investors Corp., calls for holders of the paired shares to receive $1.25 for 
each share, plus stock in a new company formed to hold Hotel Investors' Bourbon 
Street, King 8 and Gambling Hall Nevada hotels. 
