<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FTC Backs Networks: The Federal Trade Commission's Bureau of Economics 
recommended that the Federal Communications Commission repeal the so-called 
financial interest and syndication rules that prohibit the three major TV 
networks from participating in the $3-billion program rerun business. Both the 
networks and the Hollywood studios and producers are engaged in last-minute 
lobbying campaigns before the FCC makes its decision early next year. The FTC's 
BOE joins other government agencies, such as the Justice Department and the 
Commerce Department's National Telecommunications and Information 
Administration, which previously stated that they favor lifting or relaxing the 
restrictions. 
</P>
