<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 1; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
85 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Robyn Norwood and Ann Conway 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROSY PROSPECTS? Oregon, which plays Colorado State in Anaheim's Freedom Bowl 
Saturday, has followed Washington's progress with interest. . . . Washington 
plays in the Rose Bowl New Year's Day but preceded that with the Freedom Bowl 
last year and the Independence Bowl three years ago. Oregon has been following 
the same trail, starting with last year's Independence Bowl. "Next year, with 
the guys coming back, who knows, maybe the roses," says Oregon center Scot 
Boatright. Robyn Norwood and Ann Conway 
</P>
</TEXT>
