<P>
TUSTIN MARINE KILLED IN MOTORCYCLE CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TUSTIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 22-year-old Marine was killed Wednesday when his motorcycle collided with an 
18-wheel tractor-trailer rig, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, whose name was withheld pending notification of relatives, was 
pronounced dead at the scene of the 8:20 p.m. collision at the intersection of 
Red Hill and Edinger avenues, Tustin Police Lt. Frank Semelsberger said. 
</P>
<P>
The motorcyclist was believed based at the Tustin Marine Corps Helicopter Air 
Station. 
</P>
<P>
Details about the accident were sketchy, but Semelsberger said a preliminary 
investigation indicated that the motorcyclist sped through a red light in the 
southbound lanes of Red Hill Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
"For whatever reason, the driver of the truck wasn't able to stop in time to 
avoid hitting the motorcycle," he said. 
</P>
<P>
The motorcyclist was wearing a helmet at the time, as well as a heavy jacket 
and leather gloves. He was headed in the direction of the Tustin base, but it 
was not immediately known whether he was scheduled to report for duty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
