<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: MICROSEMI CORP. REPORTS LOSS OF $11.5 MILLION FOR 
FISCAL YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Microsemi Corp., the Santa Ana semiconductor company, reported a net loss of 
$11.5 million for the fiscal year ended Sept. 30, compared to a loss of $8.4 
million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue for fiscal 1990 declined 14%, to $88.9 million from $103.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
For the fourth quarter, a net loss of $11.5 million was reported, compared to a 
loss of $9.4 million for the corresponding quarter last year. Revenue fell 7%, 
to $23.5 million from $25.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the fourth-quarter results were affected by an $11-million 
reserve to cover the losses and associated costs from disposition of troubled 
businesses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
