<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Irvine Sensors Corp.: The Costa Mesa-based developer of infrared devices and 
computer electronics packages reported a net loss of $788,100 for fiscal 1990, 
compared to a loss of $833,000 last year. Revenue for the year ended Sept. 30 
rose 17%, to $3.5 million from $3 million. James Alexiou, president, attributed 
much of the year's revenue growth to the company's entry into commercial sales. 
</P>
