</P>
<P>
BARR'S HUSBAND SUES HER EX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Roseanne Barr's husband wants a gag to work -- one from a court, not from her 
hit TV show. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Arnold filed a lawsuit Wednesday in Superior Court charging that Barr's 
former husband and his attorney violated a court order by discussing the 
comic's divorce publicly. 
</P>
<P>
Arnold said ex-husband William Pentland and his attorney, palimony lawyer 
Marvin Mitchelson, discussed the divorce on the "Donahue" show in November. 
</P>
<P>
Arnold's lawyer, Martin Singer, asked a judge to sentence Mitchelson to 30 days 
in jail and Pentland to 15 days for contempt of court. Singer said Mitchelson 
"has engaged in a widespread publicity campaign to try to maliciously disparage 
and defame Tom Arnold in direct violation of the order." 
</P>
<P>
Mitchelson said he would file a countersuit, saying it was Barr who called into 
"Donahue" and discussed the divorce. She also made disparaging remarks about 
the divorce on Arsenio Hall's talk show, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Pentland, who was married for 14 years to Barr, filed a palimony lawsuit in 
August seeking at least $15 million from her and $3 million from Arnold. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
